Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.46,0:03:20.18,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Masaru Hatakeyama (28)\NGroom/Head of the Hatakeyama Group
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.46,0:03:20.18,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Miho Itō (26)\NBride
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.46,0:04:02.76,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Yuuko Hatakeyama (62)\NMasaru's mother
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.23,0:04:18.07,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kenshirō Hatakeyama (64)\NMasaru's uncle
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.28,0:04:22.53,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Arisa Hatakeyama (25)\NMasaru's cousin
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.25,0:04:39.17,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tatsuya Ishihara (37)\NMasaru's brother-in-law
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.38,0:04:44.93,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Yoshifumi Itō (25)\NMiho's brother
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.35,0:04:59.82,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Rikako Ishihara (34)\NMasaru's sister
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.40,0:00:15.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Congrats, Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.78,0:00:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.89,0:00:46.69,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Only the light of deductions can tear apart\Nblack shadows and deep darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.69,0:00:50.40,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Gunshots aimed at a newly-wedded bride and groom.\NSolve the riddle of the impossible crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.40,0:00:52.03,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.03,0:00:54.11,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.11,0:00:56.82,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.88,0:02:37.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The food's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.38,0:02:43.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did we really do the right thing coming?\NWe don't even know anyone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.89,0:02:45.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine, don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.06,0:02:49.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I'd come by myself, what table do you think I'd be seated at?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.48,0:02:53.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're all full of stuck-up old men and women.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.52,0:03:01.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when I do go to an occasion like this by myself,\Neveryone always wants to introduce me to their sons,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.74,0:03:05.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and I don't get to eat in peace!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.66,0:03:11.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess it's tough, being heiress to a financial group.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.54,0:03:15.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it is. I bet Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} feels the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.42,0:03:20.18,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Falling in love at first sight\Nwith the caretaker of his holiday villa...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.18,0:03:22.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How romantic!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.18,0:03:30.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen, I apologise for the interruption,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.89,0:03:35.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but we would like to hold a round of congratulatory messages from various speakers here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.61,0:03:39.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But before that, we have an announcement for all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.28,0:03:47.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bride and groom who have just held their solemn marriage\Nceremony at the church, Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.70,0:03:53.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,would like you to know they have already sent their\Nmarriage registration to the ward office yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.71,0:03:57.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you know about that, Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.63,0:04:00.88,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,No, I had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.88,0:04:02.76,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What a selfish thing to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.76,0:04:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like to ask for another show of applause for our happy couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.98,0:04:16.15,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What's going on now? There isn't even any wine left!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.15,0:04:18.07,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hey, Arisa! You're drinking too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.07,0:04:22.53,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You be quiet! I'm only here because you insisted I come, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.49,0:04:26.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That girl was one of the many who wanted to marry Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.29,0:04:31.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you need some wine? I'll bring some straightaway.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.62,0:04:37.29,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yoshifumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you're the bride's brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.29,0:04:39.17,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You should let someone else take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.17,0:04:42.84,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's fine. I don't really like sitting still.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.84,0:04:45.51,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm more comfortable when I'm up and about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.35,0:04:51.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He should've let himself relax today, at least...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.56,0:04:54.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once a caretaker, always a caretaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.02,0:05:00.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Honestly! It's hard to bear thinking that that woman\Nwill have the Hatakeyama fortune at her fingertips.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.57,0:05:03.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Father will be turning in his grave!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.41,0:05:10.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, we will begin with a message\Nfrom Kenshirō Hatakeyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.70,0:05:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the uncle of the newly-wedded Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nand the president of Hatakeyama Bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.04,0:05:19.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.92,0:05:21.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've gotta go to the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.26,0:05:27.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.43,0:05:30.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it? Need the toilet?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.51,0:05:31.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.64,0:05:32.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know where to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.98,0:05:34.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.02,0:05:39.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the boy here with the Suzuki\NFinancial Group's heiress, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.69,0:05:44.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! You're the caretaker for this villa, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.11,0:05:54.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. When the villa was first built, my mum and\Ndad took care of it, but they both died in an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.83,0:05:57.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you do before then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.46,0:05:59.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was a farmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.46,0:06:03.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in this area, most of the crops tend\Nto be eaten by monkeys and boars.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.71,0:06:07.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I stopped farming and took over looking after the villa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.89,0:06:11.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But never mind that, didn't you need the toilet?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.22,0:06:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I forgot. See ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.98,0:06:22.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you believe he said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.52,0:06:23.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hi, how are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.74,0:06:27.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hope you enjoyed the food?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.78,0:06:31.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. We've all eaten our fill.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.33,0:06:32.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm glad to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.53,0:06:39.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we get back from our honeymoon,\Nthe three of you should visit us in Tōkyō!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.04,0:06:42.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course. But bring us back some souvenirs!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.09,0:06:46.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, I'll make sure not to forget!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.38,0:06:49.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, should you really be away from your bride's side?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.26,0:06:52.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She might get jealous of you talking with two beautiful girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.76,0:06:55.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, don't worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.97,0:06:58.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I trust Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.10,0:07:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, what passion!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.31,0:07:03.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you don't look too well...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.07,0:07:06.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right... I'm just feeling a little tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.90,0:07:11.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why don't you leave the rest to me,\Nand you can go back to the hotel and rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.99,0:07:12.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshifumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.78,0:07:13.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.83,0:07:15.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you drink anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.49,0:07:17.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. I don't drink alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.54,0:07:22.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I'm sorry to bother you, but\Ncould you take Miho there in my car?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.08,0:07:22.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.80,0:07:35.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should get going soon too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.56,0:07:36.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.89,0:07:39.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then let's say goodbye to Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.31,0:07:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Where's Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.23,0:07:45.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He got a call from Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} about ten minutes ago and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.77,0:07:47.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It's a disaster!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.24,0:07:49.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.86,0:07:55.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-By the estate cars in the c-car park...\NT-The groom is collapsed on the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.99,0:07:57.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.12,0:07:59.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.83,0:08:00.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.51,0:08:14.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He's been shot from close range...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.26,0:08:15.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.10,0:08:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.06,0:08:19.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't come any closer until the police get here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.43,0:08:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.73,0:08:21.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.35,0:08:23.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quick, get the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.06,0:08:28.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that really Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} lying there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.65,0:08:29.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.61,0:08:34.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that sound?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.41,0:08:36.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It came from across the river...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.16,0:08:38.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it sounded like it came from the hotel...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.87,0:08:39.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.56,0:09:02.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.12,0:09:20.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.58,0:09:28.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, except for Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, this is everyone who was\Nhere when you heard what sounded like a gunshot?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.50,0:09:34.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} called us and said we should\Nall wait here until the police arrived...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.09,0:09:37.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay. Then let's go and check the other crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.89,0:09:38.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.99,0:10:01.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you doing, Detective Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.62,0:10:06.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, we're looking for anything the killer might've left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.29,0:10:08.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've found something!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.50,0:10:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This looks like it must be the murder weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.88,0:10:15.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me! We need to take some photos!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.80,0:10:18.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Bamboo...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.59,0:10:21.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why is bamboo here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.56,0:10:32.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, I'm sorry for asking at such a trying time, but\Nwhat's going to happen to the shares Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} held?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.65,0:10:35.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm concerned that the employees will be worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.86,0:10:43.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, he didn't have any children, so wouldn't they\Ngo to our mother, and me because I'm his sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.08,0:10:54.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. If Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was to die before Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, everything\NMasaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} owned would become Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s when he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.55,0:10:57.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.09,0:10:59.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you hear the announcement last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.63,0:11:02.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Their marriage has already been registered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.93,0:11:05.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then what happens to Masaru's fortune?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.52,0:11:13.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was to die after Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r},\Nthen Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s family would inherit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.94,0:11:17.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.36,0:11:21.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll never accept that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.82,0:11:24.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whether you do or not, it's the law...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.41,0:11:28.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it's a {\i1}stupid{\i0} law!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.83,0:11:36.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to bring you all here at a time like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.92,0:11:40.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My mother had to go and lie down\Nin her room because of the shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.97,0:11:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.05,0:11:45.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Out of everyone that was here yesterday,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.47,0:11:51.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've had everyone who had concrete alibis for both\Nof their estimated times of death leave already.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.31,0:11:54.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you suspect all of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.81,0:12:01.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's just that you all have deep\Nconnections with the two victims,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.03,0:12:05.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and so while I know you must be angry,\NI hope you will help our investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.37,0:12:12.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and I were by Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s\Ncorpse when Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.29,0:12:15.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have an alibi for Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s murder at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.09,0:12:25.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. The bullets we recovered from both bodies were\Nboth shot from the gun found in the flower bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.47,0:12:30.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, we believe they were\Nboth murdered by the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.73,0:12:32.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we're fine...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.10,0:12:37.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But at the time, Rikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Arisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nyou had already returned to the hotel, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.98,0:12:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you calling me a murderer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.40,0:12:43.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now, don't take this personally...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.20,0:12:45.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're just discussing the possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.95,0:12:53.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the successive murders of the bride and groom have only\Noccurred yesterday, we have yet to discover the culprit's motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.96,0:12:58.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we do have questions for\Nthe bride's brother, Yoshifumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.55,0:13:01.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.05,0:13:05.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In our investigation since last night,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.80,0:13:11.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we've discovered that you are several\Nmillion yen in debt to various banks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.31,0:13:14.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.31,0:13:18.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you or aren't you? We need an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.90,0:13:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. I am indeed in debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.44,0:13:25.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I didn't kill anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.57,0:13:27.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would I kill my sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.16,0:13:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's the only family I had left...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.16,0:13:36.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Detective Chiba, what were you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.71,0:13:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.08,0:13:40.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was checking the surveillance footage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.63,0:13:47.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The surveillance camera just inside the entrance shows\Nthe area by the flower bed where we found the gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.93,0:13:51.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I thought I'd check all the recordings from yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.97,0:13:54.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But nobody went near the flower bed...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.35,0:13:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why was the gun there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.40,0:14:01.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe someone threw it from a window upstairs in the hotel...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.82,0:14:12.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What are these four imprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.21,0:14:24.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I got a call last night saying the lamppost there had gone out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.67,0:14:26.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you were there, did you see anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.01,0:14:29.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.39,0:14:39.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.44,0:14:43.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see, it must've been...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.78,0:14:50.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I got the call at 9:40, so it must've been about 9:45.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.20,0:14:52.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}9:45...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.49,0:14:54.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What could that mean...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.37,0:15:01.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}At 9:45, Miho{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} had only {\i1}just{\i0} left the villa...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.63,0:15:05.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's half an hour before we\Ndiscovered Masaru{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.80,0:15:14.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.51,0:15:16.72,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But then that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.72,0:15:17.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.44,0:15:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A little kid shouldn't be walking around this early.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.44,0:15:23.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.36,0:15:28.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of hungry monkeys in the\Narea, so you'll end up getting bitten!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.45,0:15:33.58,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Right, if someone used that...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.58,0:15:36.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What reason would I have to murder Masaru?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.74,0:15:44.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wanted to get rid of Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} so your own husband\Ncould run the Hatakeyama Group, didn't you? I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.00,0:15:47.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a ridiculous accusation, you stupid little girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.76,0:15:51.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You probably killed Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} because\Nshe stopped you from marrying Masaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.63,0:15:54.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then you even killed Masaru when he found out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.80,0:15:56.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now who's the idiot here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.68,0:15:59.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was shot first!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.64,0:16:02.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You want his money so much you can't even think clearly?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.69,0:16:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's enough, you should be ashamed of yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.11,0:16:08.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.94,0:16:10.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.03,0:16:13.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should be leav—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.12,0:16:17.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko, is this it? Your thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.95,0:16:23.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to say anything if I didn't have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.37,0:16:26.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if I don't say something, the\Nkiller is the only one who'd benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.67,0:16:31.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you mean you've figured out who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.84,0:16:40.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes... And if the police had just arrested the culprit in the\Nfirst place, there wouldn't be any need for all this arguing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.35,0:16:44.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, there's one thing that you did get right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.11,0:16:49.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the first one murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.36,0:16:50.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.90,0:16:55.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the only ones who went back to the\Nhotel early were Rikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Arisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.28,0:16:57.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you, I'm not a murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.41,0:16:58.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me either!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.20,0:17:01.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know that you two didn't kill anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.79,0:17:07.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It happened not long after Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had arrived at her cottage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.00,0:17:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why she hadn't changed out of her dress...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.25,0:17:15.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You probably drove Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} back, then\Nwasted no time murdering her, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.68,0:17:16.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshifumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.89,0:17:20.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.39,0:17:23.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're in a lot of debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.06,0:17:31.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When your sister was to be married, you thought she could\Nrepay your debts, but things didn't go as you had hoped.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.65,0:17:37.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you slipped something into your sister's drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.12,0:17:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When she started feeling unwell, you took her back to her\Ncottage and murdered her with a gun you'd hidden there...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.21,0:17:46.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Silencing the noise with something like a cushion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.75,0:17:54.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, you used Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s phone to call out\NMasaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and murdered him just like Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.80,0:18:01.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just hold on a minute! What about the gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.31,0:18:03.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was found in the hotel flower beds, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.73,0:18:08.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I stayed with everyone beside Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} until the police arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.44,0:18:11.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never had time to put the gun there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.32,0:18:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what bothered me the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.49,0:18:17.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did the killer choose to put the gun there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.12,0:18:20.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then I figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.83,0:18:25.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The gun wasn't put there manually —\hit {\i1}landed{\i0} there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.08,0:18:31.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The villa and hotel roughly face each\Nother on either side of the river, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.71,0:18:37.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it'd be impossible to throw the gun to the\Nother shore by hand after murdering Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.51,0:18:39.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you used that instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.94,0:18:49.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would I do that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.85,0:18:51.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.81,0:18:54.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even Rikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Arisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} mentioned why.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.40,0:19:05.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had to make it look like Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died after Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} so\Nthat Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fortune would have been passed to Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.12,0:19:09.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To do that, the gun had to be found on this side of the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.96,0:19:14.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You're just guessing! Do you have any proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.59,0:19:18.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you remember seeing a man carrying a ladder?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.22,0:19:28.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A hotel employee came to replace a lamp on the path to the\Ncottages, and remembers seeing someone leaving her cottage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.18,0:19:31.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before Masaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.23,0:19:35.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, you murdered Miho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.65,0:19:40.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then what was that gunshot we all heard at the car park?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.15,0:19:46.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That gunshot was the heart of the alibi you so cleverly devised.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.54,0:19:49.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, come on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.29,0:19:54.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like you've seen it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.88,0:19:58.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it was found in your shed, so of course you would have.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.80,0:20:01.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.30,0:20:03.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A {\i1}suzume-odoshi{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.30,0:20:09.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a tool used to stop tree sparrows from eating rice plants\Nplanted in autumn by driving them away with fireworks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.81,0:20:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently, they're used in this area to drive away monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.82,0:20:21.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, it was set to only sound once.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.11,0:20:23.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It made the sound that everyone heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.16,0:20:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it! This was all my sister's fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.33,0:20:36.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was marrying into a family with billions,\Nbut wouldn't give me anything at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.55,0:20:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you ever heard of someone so heartless?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.85,0:22:16.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ran looks very depressed today.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.43,0:22:20.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Well, given what happened, I guess it's no surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.90,0:22:25.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, tonight you should have\Na tasty meal and cheer yourself up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.23,0:22:27.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll even make you dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.78,0:22:33.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw a cooking show on TV recently which\Nshowed how to make a really nice curry!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.83,0:22:39.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! Curry's no good! It's full of calories.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.79,0:22:45.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We did just go through that really sad case, but when\NI got back from the wedding and weighed myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.25,0:22:50.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd put on 2 kg! Isn't that shocking?! 2 kg!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.80,0:22:54.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is {\i1}that{\i0} why you're so depressed...?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.35,0:22:55.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.06,0:22:57.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.93,0:22:58.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.27,0:23:03.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko... You don't look happy...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.06,0:23:08.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen to this! When I got back from the\Nwedding and weighed myself, I'd put on 3 kg!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.94,0:23:13.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I put on 2 kg too! We've gotta\Nslim down before the summer!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.07,0:23:14.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our swimsuits won't fit!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.95,0:23:19.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't school weight check day coming up before that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.75,0:23:22.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, what're we gonna do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.46,0:23:25.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have to exercise! Let's run, Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.08,0:23:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.96,0:23:27.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.92,0:23:32.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}My, my... I'll end up losing weight worrying about them...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.35,0:23:37.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,G-Great luck?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.81,0:23:41.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just witnessed a murder taking place!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.53,0:23:49.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan Special:\N'Jodie's Memories and the Flower Viewing Trap'!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.25,0:23:54.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: A five yen coin!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.25,0:23:56.00,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next week, an hour-long special!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.00,0:23:59.34,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's filled with the FBI and Men in Black!
